Employees receive training in the procedures to be followed by employees who remain to operate critical plant operations before they evacuate. Aspen has around-the-clock communications capability with appropriate emergency response organizations (Fire Department, Police, Sheriff's Office, or similar). This interface provides the means of notifying the public of an incident, if necessary, as well as facilitating quick response to an incident. In addition, Aspen conducts periodic emergency drills and annual refresher training for plant personnel.



Q. Planned changes to improve safety



Aspen's management is committed to the following:



1. Preventing accidents;

2. Training our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;

3. Participating in community emergency preparedness;

4. Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with Aspen operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents.

With these objectives in mind, this Risk Management Plan has been developed to provide information about our management of the risks associated with the natural gas treatment and liquids recovery process. Most importantly, we stress our commitment to ensuring a safe operation for our employees, our visitors, and our community.
